<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{7}{y}={43}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+{4}{y}={15}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1},{5}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -5. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{5}}{{-{{8}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{5}}}{{-{{8}}}}{\left(-{8}{x}+{7}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{5}}}{{-{{8}}}}{\left({43}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({5}\right)}{x}+{4.375}{y}={26.875}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+{4}{y}={15}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8.375}{y}={41.875}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{41.875}}{{8.375}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={5}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{7}{\left({5}\right)}={43}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{\left({35}\right)}={43}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}={43}-{\left({35}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{8}}{{-{{8}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{1}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1},{5}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>